experiment.name: NMC
experiment.exp_info:
The proton structure function F2p measured by the NMC Collaboration in muon p deep inelastic scattering from the merged data sets at incident momenta 90, 120, 200 and 280 GeV. Data cover the x range 0.002 to 0.6 and Q^2 range from 0.5 to 75 GeV^2. This data is the final full NMC data set and supersedes any previous NMC data. The structure function F2p averaged over measurements for all energies and both triggers with the normalisation corrections (see Table 2 in the paper). The results are the statistically weighted averages given at the centre of each (x,Q**2)-bin. The values of R are those used in the analysis ie. for x below 0.12 values obtained from NMC data (these analysis) and for higher x Slac R(1990). In the last column we give the values of F2(R1990) obtained using the values of R(1990) from the parameterisation given in the paper Whitlow et al, Phys.Lett.B250(1990)193, for all x values.
